# ChangeLog

## v0.93.0

### Bug Fixes
- CTC channel chaining now uses ring topology (ch3→ch0) matching VHDL
- +3 ROM-high bit via port 0x1FFD now observable + NR 0x82 bit 3 gating
- Specdrum port 0xDF read handler for VHDL port_1f combo gate
- I2C ACK phase off-by-one — read data was shifted left by one bit

### Internal JNEXT Development
- Subsystem compliance tests: 1086/1086 pass, 0 fail (696 skip)
- Regression suite: 34/34 clean
- Uniform test output format across all 19 test suites
- Color-coded `make unit-test` target with per-suite totals
- Version bumping procedure documented in CLAUDE.md

## v0.92.0

### User Features
- 640px native framebuffer for tilemap 80-col and Layer 2 640x256 modes
- Floating bus emulation enabled for all machine types
- Compositor blend modes 110 (additive) and 111 (subtractive)
- Pentagon, Kempston joystick, mouse, and ULA+ ports now respond

### Developer Features
- Debugger: improved interrupt and tilemap split-screen debugging

### Bug Fixes
- Z80 instruction timing and contention fixes — games now run at correct speed
- NEX loader: palette, sprite, transparency, and init fixes
- Tilemap rendering, scrolling, control-bit swap, and 80-col pixel addressing
- Compositor NR 0x14 palette-compare transparency for ULA and Layer 2
- Port dispatch exclusive routing and VHDL-correct decode masks
- NR 0x82-0x85 port-enable register defaults and gating
- DivMMC mapram OR-latch, read_control mask, ROM3 automap gating
- DMA prescaler, ULA frame timing, AY envelope, SPI decode, MMU reset

### Internal JNEXT Development
- Subsystem compliance tests: 1150/1171 pass (98%)
- Regression suite: 34/34 clean
- 15 emulator fixes + 9 test reclassifications across 21 backlog items

## v0.91.0

### User Features
- ZX Spectrum 48K, 128K, +2A/+3, Pentagon, and Next machine types
- ULA, Layer 2 (256/320/640), Sprites (8-bit/4-bit), Tilemap, Copper
- 6-mode layer compositor with per-scanline border colour
- 8 palettes with 9-bit RGB (512 colours)
- AY/YM x3 TurboSound, 4-channel DAC, Beeper
- NEX, SNA, SZX, TAP, TZX, WAV, RZX file formats
- Qt 6 GUI: Hi-DPI, fullscreen, CRT filter, speed control, screenshots, MPEG4 video recording

### Developer Features
- Debugger: registers, disassembly, hex editor, breakpoints, trace, symbol tables
- Magic breakpoint (ED FF / DD 01) and magic debug port
- Headless mode for automated testing and screenshot regression suite
- Backwards execution: Step Back, Frame Back, rewind slider

### Bug Fixes
- (initial release)

### Internal JNEXT Development
- FUSE-based Z80 core with Z80N extensions (26 opcodes)
- Memory contention for 48K, 128K, +3, Pentagon timing models
- IM1/IM2 interrupt controller with 14 Next interrupt levels
- DivMMC with automap, CTC, UART, DMA, SPI, I2C/RTC peripherals
